# Product Development Rules — Trivense vs Tricount

Primary competitor: [Tricount](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.tribab.tricount.android)

Goal: faster, simpler, more modern, better for India/travelers/power users — NOT a clone.

## Out of scope (do not build or suggest)

**Photos / receipts** — no receipt attach, receipt gallery, or photo upload on expenses. Do not propose parity with Tricount photo sharing for bills.

**AI features** — no OCR, auto-categorization via ML, voice/NL expense entry, AI summaries, anomaly detection, or other AI/ML-powered features. Prefer simple rules, smart defaults, and clear UX instead.

If Tricount has photos/AI-like capabilities, **do not copy them**. Compete on split/settle, boards, analytics, export, sync, and pricing — not photos or AI.

## Before every change

1. Does Tricount have this? How do they solve it?
2. Can we simplify, speed up, or automate without AI?
3. Retention, reviews, premium potential?
4. Never implement just because it exists — and never implement out-of-scope items above.

## Feature removal

Never remove without checking Tricount. If Tricount has it → do not remove; improve, premium-gate, optionalize, or redesign. Remove only if UX harm, confusion, duplication, or zero usage.

## Mandatory analysis format

For feature discussions provide: Tricount (has/how/strengths/weaknesses), Our app (current/gaps/UX wins), Recommendation (KEEP | IMPROVE | REDESIGN | ADD | REMOVE).

## UX priorities

Less taps/typing, smart defaults (non-AI), offline-first, fast load, one-handed use, clear empty states & onboarding, dark mode, accessibility.

## Automation (allowed, non-AI)

Settlement math, split calculations, budget alerts, recurring reminders (rule-based), export formatting, sync — no machine learning required.

## Premium classification

Every feature: Free | Premium | Enterprise — with WHY.

## Engineering

Clean architecture, offline-first, optimistic UI, background sync, Supabase RLS, indexing, performance.

## Decision framework

If a request makes us worse than Tricount → stop, explain, suggest better. If Tricount solves it better → explain theirs, propose improved version. If we lack parity → flag immediately.

## Response footer (feature/product work)

End with **Competitive Assessment**: parity %, UX improvement, performance, complexity, user value, should implement, plus 2–5 competitive improvements.
